Testing (updated 20150504)
==========================

More general information needed here, but for now, here's how
to recreate a specific failure in test run03.

1) Get the tarball from ~cornell/dw_miscompare_20150504

2) untar into <dir>

3) cd <dir>/libhio-0.1

4) module swap PrgEnv-cray PrgEnv-gnu
    module load craype-haswell cray-mpich

5) ./configure

6) make all

7) cd <dir>/libhio-0.1/tests

8) Create a directory in DW
    e.g. aprun -b mkdir /dwphase1/cornell/hio_test2

9) export HIO_ROOT=<DW DIR>
    export HIO_ROOT=/dwphase1/cornell/hio_test2

10) ./run03 -d 4 -v 3 -n 256 -s m 1>run03.db01.out 2>&1

11) grep miscompare run03.db*.out 

12) Parameters to run03 are:

  Syntax:
    ./run03
        [-s <size>]
        [-n <num_ranks>]
        [-v <verb_level>]
        [-d <debug_level>]

  Options:
    -s <size>       Per rank run size t|s|m|l|x  (default s)
    -n <num_ranks>  Number of MPI ranks.  Default is all allocated
                    CPs or 2 on Mac OS
    -v <verb_lev>   Verbosity level for xexec2, default 1
    -d <debug_lev>  Debug level for xexec2, default 0

The test driver xexec2 has a bit of help text that will describe the
parameters in run03.

--- End of README ---


